</CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF=http://www.ezboard.com><IMG SRC=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/banners/effreeti_ED.gif BORDER=0></A><P></CENTER><TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>The Druids Grove</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicstories><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Druidic Stories</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Amazing near death escapes... lets here about them</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicstories.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/newtopic.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; &nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicstories.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicstories.showMessage?topicID=153.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#f7f5e6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/ukeeth07.showPublicProfile>keeth07</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>6/20/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>9:55:50 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Amazing near death escapes... lets here about them</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ok here is my story and I am still not sure how I was this lucky.  I am in W Karana hutning bandits on the hill above the farm.  We are off to the left on the side closest to the farm.  I am grouped with another druid both of us at level 12.  We harmony the camp and pull a bandit out with root.  Suddenly in it's path spawns a caster... DOH  ok we are still ok it will just be painful. Then another bandit and a brigand are running up from the downhill forest camp and decide to jump into the fray.  ok now neither of us has sow and we are gettign pounded.  Instead of us both dieing I tell my comrade to run and jump into the fray grabbing the attention of al but one bandit.  so now i am being pounded by  a bandit, brigand , and bandit caster.  As i watch my hp plummet I figure may as well try a gate .. gate just about to go off when the bandit gives me the finishing blow and I see the dreaded message YOU HAVE BEEN KNOCKED UNCONCIOUS&quot;.  Just as I start ranting and raving about the heritage of bandits, i see you regain concentration and continue casting.  LOADING PLEASE WAIT.  I appear at my bind spot laying on the ground with my HP bar 1/4 of the purple left.  Luckily no newbie bug came and killed me ( in qeynos newbie zone )  I was thrilled and overjoyed at living when i had already considered myself dead.   Anyway that is the closest I have come to dieing and lived.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#e6ebd7><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uskeeja.showPublicProfile>Skeeja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>6/26/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>3:35:22 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Amazing near death escapes... lets here about them</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The other day in Kedge, I decide to pull the Hammerhead shark...big mistake...I swim as fast as I can back to the zone, he is really hitting me hard, and I don't warn my party of inc, because I am trying to get out before dying...I made zone with so few hp, that there is no red, but I made it...unfortunately, my party tried to fight it, and 2 of the other 5 were killed, due to my stupidity...luckily we had a Cleric there who rezzed them, after I had to lure the shark away from the zone again (Sharks won't leave the zone if trained there for some reason...)</font><P>Skeeja Skywolf <BR>
Druid of the 44th Era <BR>
The Tribunal <BR><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#f7f5e6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/umyttenalipes.showPublicProfile>Mytten Alipes</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>6/26/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>4:00:23 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Amazing near death escapes... lets here about them</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well my best close brush with death was in Najena. After going in to the portal in Najena things got a bit out of hand and we got a nice train after us. And not a normal 2-3 mob train. This train consisted of a couple of enchanters,  three or so elementals and a couple of Tentacle terrors.<br>
<br>
I am madly running towards the zone and i am watching my HP bar drop rapidly. I am almost at the zone with a bubble left when i get rooted. So i stand there and see my bar drop to three quarter, half, a quarter. Then a Tentacle terror releases his knock spell on me and knocks me over the zone border breaking the root. I zoned into Lavastorm with seven HP left. <br>
<br>
Saved by a MOB spell.<br>
<br>
Mytten Alipes<br>
Brell Serilis<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#e6ebd7><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uskeeja.showPublicProfile>Skeeja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>7/1/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>9:09:49 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Amazing near death escapes... lets here about them</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Here's an interesting one that happened to me right after Kunark came out.  The very first time I port over there and walk through the Ice Tunnel, I get attacked by a Spider.  Now these things cast a nasty dot (Stinging swarm.  Perhaps you heard of it?)  Anyway, I tried to run, and it roots me, and then I see You have died...I return to my bind point (the Druid circle, I like to save that 230 mana hehe), with no spells, items or mana.  I say WTF, I never had that happen before...but when I checked my exp, I hadn't lost any :)  The first time I ever heard of not losing exp upon a death, apparently if you die to a DoT, you don't lose exp.  So I blithely walk back to the tunnel, loot my body, and med up.  The one time I didn't mind dying:)<br>
</font><P>Skeeja Skywolf <BR>
Druid of the 44th Era <BR>
The Tribunal <BR><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#f7f5e6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/utalysian45.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talysian45</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>8/29/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>4:26:21 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.phantommessenger.com/talysian/wolf04.jpg width=100 height=73></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Amazing near death escapes... lets here about them</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The closest I ever came to dying *without* dying was as a newbie (lvl 4) in Greater Shoutdark.  I was fighting a spiderling (and winning =) ) when two of his buddies decided to help out.  I knew I couldn't handle all of them, so I ran like a girlie-man for the guards.  Got there and turned around to watch Guard Soandso KILL 'em.  Well, just before he got the last one, it bit ME for 3 points and I fell unconscious.  And then I noticed I was poisoned.  I noticed this 'cause I kept getting the message &quot;YOU are bleeding to death&quot;.  Actually, I got spammed with it.  hehe  And I'm lying there unconscious and watching my purple go and can't do anything.  Can't yell for help, can't ask for a heal, can't speak and I'm bleeding to death.  As I hit the last bub of purple, I get &quot;The poison has run it's course.&quot;  Cool!  Oh wait, the purple is still dropping!  It got down to about an eighth of a bub before it started to rise.  I don't want to EVER get that close again or feel that helpless.  ('Course, it's better than dying, I suppose. lol)<br>
<br>
Life is good.<br>
<br>
[Edit - spelling and grammar.  =/ ]</font><P><font color="#0000d0"><b>Talysian<br><font face="comic sans ms" size="1" color="#0000e0">Woodelf Druid of Bristlebane<br><font color="#d00000">4th</font> <font color="#b00000">Circle of Mysticals</font><br><center><font color="#009966" size="2">Bursting forth with the power of ten BILLION butterfly sneezes</b></font></center></font><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/utalysian45.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talysian45</A> at: 8/29/00 7:25:26 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#e6ebd7><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=birdley>birdley</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>9/21/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>11:11:52 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Closest call</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">When I was 29th level, I kited Avocets in SK.  Well I didn't have enough mana back then to nuke them all the way down so I had to thorn up, dot and melee a bit at the end.  Well sometimes I'd get partial or full resists and that could make it a really close fight at the end.  Twice(!) it happened that the Avocet killed me but also killed itself on my damage shield.  Happily, it turns out that simultaneous death like that favors the player because you get the XP for the mob and lose none for the death.  </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#f7f5e6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquillarstav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QuillarStav</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>10/31/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>12:03:56 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Closest call</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I love these stories.  My group was AoEing in Solusek B on fire imps.  We had a bard pulling, and somehow aggroed around 5 or 6 of them (only one group).  Our wizard and cleric dropped and I got the evac call, well, after the wizard and cleric, guess who was next on the aggro list :/ <br>
(three upheavals for ~2000 damage to 5 fire imps will do that).  I hit evac and got beat down.  I got hit for over 400 damage in about 6 hits.  I made it with 27 hp left and got dropped somewhere near Kaladim.  My party, what was left of it, made it to the druid ring.  Fun stuff.<br>
<br>
Another good one happened yesterday.  We were in the hole doing the last step for the Shammy uber quest.  We got @#%$y and the room filled up with mobs.  He looted what he needed, our enchanters were dead, tanks were all but dead and I hit evac.  About 3 seconds into the cast I was summoned.  Fortunately I ran into a corner before i evaced and thus i hightailed it back to that corner.  Little known fact is that if you move or are knocked back while casting, if you can make it back to your exact point, youre spell will go off (very usefull for evacs).  So i got the 4 live members out of the Hole with that one.  Fun stuff that you just can't experience solo :)  </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#e6ebd7><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucelaenoblackbird.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celaeno Blackbird</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>11/11/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>3:03:45 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My date with the Avatar of Fear</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Stupid death, close escape, vengeance, this has it all :)<br>
(Can't play EQ now and will have to retire completely at the end of the month so I might start posting instead?)<br>
<br>
Lvl 34 and still in CT, I logged in and joined a group in Silver Temple. As I head to the temple yard, one of the monks is saying that the AoF has spawned in the wrong place. <br>
*Bad feeling* <br>
They assure me that the AoF isn't in my path, I go in, find the group, the monk is feigning, I ask what they want me to do... next thing I know, the AoF and friends are beating on us. Someone is yelling to evac, I wonder if they mean me, try to invis and mem one of my gates and the AoF is all over me. Ouch. I am no longer invisible and the AoF is beating on someone else and I do something I hope I won't do again in my remaining playtime: I panic and run. Visible. Past a lot of lizards. At least I didn't train the AoF to zone... I made it to just inside the double doors to the zone when a broodling decided to slap me and there I am sitting naked on the Feerott side :\ Turns out that amongst the casters in the group I'd just joined was not one but two wizards, one of them was designated evac'er and had gated pretty much everyone else out. If I had stayed put, I would have survived. To top it off I conveniently had a root in one of my inventory spots, which I left on my body, but never managed to find a cleric :\<br>
<br>
Swear to never hunt in CT again unless it's hunting the AoF (I have two other stupid deaths there), and to never panic again.<br>
<br>
That evening, a monk friend of mine asks me to come back to CT, where he is starting an AoF group. Vengeance time? I gate back, join the group, we invis and head for the AoF. I get to swim through a pretty green bubble and we set up camp in the little side room. Monk, druid, chanter, rogue, cleric and I think a SK. Monk does his crazy monk puller thing (which he is very good at) and pulls appropriate amounts of lizards and alligator while we wait for the Hairy Ugly One. I'm DS'ing, snaring, str buffing and taming the occasional alligator when the AoF spawns. How we knew he'd spawned? I was writhing in the grip of agony, he's hitting me HARD, and I resist his Scarecrow fear spell (Did my endure magic have anything to do with that? I don't know but I am still glad I chose that occasion to buff with it)<br>
I move away so the others can get him off me, cleric heals me up from 2 bubbles, I get mad. Screw mana conservation, I'm going to make that guy PAY! So, I dot him and start nuking with immolate (yes, resists and all that but he wasn't at prime health when I started and they all landed pretty well) while the monk and rogue are beating on him. Third immolate lands: You have slain the Avatar of Fear!  Vengeance is mine!<br>
Inspect: He has the BP. The rogue has mostly RS except the coif and that piece, so we dress him up in all black :)<br>
<br>
We kill some more stuff, people have to leave. We lose the enchanter, cleric and tank, enlist a new enchanter, send the enchanter to pick up a new cleric and tank in the courtyard since I am reluctant to guide people somewhere I've gone *once*, monk peeks around while rogue and I wait... I make a comment about how the AoF maybe shouldn't attack people who worshipped fear, and I guess he heard me because the next thing I know, he is back and beating on me, again. The guy just loves me, it seems :) <br>
The monk later stated that he'd peeked down the ramp and seen the hairy brute charging him and almost begun to cry; odds were pretty good he was going to wipe the floor with us. I'm at less than half a bubble of health and throw a gHeal or two on myself in case something else wants a piece of me, cast evac and wait for 9 nervewracking seconds while monk and rogue beat on him and yell evac at me... next thing we know we're all in EK, alive and on one hell of an adrenaline rush :)<br>
<br>
Back to Cazic, pick up cleric, chanter and new tank in the courtyard, return to the area through the pools, pull the bastard and kill him a second time. Claws drop. Wanted them for my baby woodelf warrior, but lost the roll so she'll have to wait. The evening proceeded with highlvl people from the rogue's guild stopping by, including a cleric in Robe of the Seeker who buffed us and bought my splitpaw gloves off my hands for 50 pp. (He was auctioning for gloves and a crude stein so he could complete the 'caster' look and thoroughly confuse people :) )<br>
<br>
AoF popped a final time before we finish, unfortunately he spawned in the wrong place again and dropped a BP to some highlvl people hanging around the silver temple area. Oh well, can't have them all. It was good fun, great revenge, and now I have Guk to get bewildered in :) <br>
<br>
(This story was brought to you by a fit of boredom)<br>
<br>
</font><P><center><font size="-1">
<b>Celaeno Blackbird</b><br>
<i>Druid of the 35th Circle, Erollisi Marr<br>
Elven Wrath Coalition Officer<br>
Karana worshipper by heart</i></font></center><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#f7f5e6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rainfall>Rainfall</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>11/14/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>9:40:45 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Don't snare yourself...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This is probably my closest-to-death-but-didn't-die experience. I was solo kiting mammoths in Everfrost, and had just found one when sow began to wear off. The zone was fairly crowded, with a lot of people killing mammoths, so I wanted to make sure I got this one. I figured I could snare the mammoth, then cast sow on myself. <br>
<br>
Well, I cast snare on the mob, it was resisted. Ack! So I run away and try to get enough time to cast sow on myself. I successfully cast sow, and then turn around to snare the mammoth. Unfortunately, I had forgot to re-target the mammoth after sowing myself. The result? I snared myself! Of course this also canceled sow. <br>
<br>
So now I'm sitting there hardly able to move with this mammoth gorring (or whatever its called) me for 50+ points of damage. Hmm...what to do?<br>
<br>
Luckily, I had gate memmed, and luckily somehow I got it off. So I pop up at my bind point (half way across the zone). I still have 75m, so I figure maybe I can finish the fight.<br>
<br>
Quickly I mem cancel magic, remove the snare, and re sow myself. Then I med a bit. Just as I get 85m or so, the mammoth shows up. I quickly snare HIM, and proceed to kite him to death. Phew! <br>
<br>
Well thats my near death story...also of note: one level ago I was kiting tesch mas gnolls and snared myself...that time I DID die hehe<br>
<br>
Rainfall<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#e6ebd7><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulillianasweetleaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lilliana Sweetleaf</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>11/25/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>10:09:17 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">hehe</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><br>
<br>
Being a somewhat masochistic druid, I like to go charm bats and solo LDCs from time to time.  This usually results in my untimely demise or gate, but every now and then it turns out profitable.<br>
<br>
