<img src="http://www.geocities.com/mayvillegobs/images/thereal.gif"><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#e6ebd7><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=theonius>Theonius</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>12/4/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>10:33:07 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">lol check this one out</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This was my first encounter with Nagnafen.  I was about lvl 42 then.  I was wandering around sol b looking for the priest group when I came to a large mansion looking like place.  I decided to check it out, so I carefully looked inside the door and saw that no mobs were there, I was told later by a friend that the fire giants should have been there but someone must have been pulling them.  As I wandered around inside I finnally got to the other side of the castle and lo and behold it led to a large cavern and Nagnafen was just sitting there.  I just sat there in disbelief, cofident that I was out of his range.  After about 5 seconds the beast charged. Lol i almost pissed in my pants. He came right at me.  I couldn't react in time he was upon me in seconds.  He hit me 3 times for 250ish each, then cast fear on me.  lol that saved me.  I ran back like 2 steps and I was outside the area that he would follow.  Lol I had actually lived.  I remembered hearing that dragons could summon so I warped away, only to later learn that Nagnafen can't summon hehehehe.  It was a pretty cool encounter</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#f7f5e6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwildarianaturesong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wildaria Naturesong</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>12/7/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>9:11:46 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Amazing near death escapes... lets here about them</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Let me set the scene here...<br>
I'm a 12th season druid fighting in Crushbone. I've travelled around a lot and been all the way to Freeport and back (twice).  I've previously fought monsters as tough as Legionnaires in a small two person group at level 10, with a high level druid casting buffs and heals every so often and got all the way to level 11.  So I go off and join another group later and fight larger numbers of monsters with the same results and got to level 12. So, proud of myself as I am, I decide to join a Throne Room group and were doing amazingly well, until... You guessed it, the morons in the tower camping Crush forgot that D'Vinn also spawned there. They, being low on health after their last Crush encounter, get slaughtered right in front of our little group, and I foolishly decide to heal my friends... Wrong stupid thing to do, so now I have D'Vinn whooping up and right then, the RG comes out, the legionnaires spawn, the Emissary spawns and all hell breaks loose.  So I, being the creative person that I am, decide to jump out the window behind the door. (those of you that know the spot and the NPC pathing bugs know this is a great tactic, as long as you don't fall in the moat) Anyway, he slaughters my group except for me and my friend who saw me jump out and followed me quickly. It doesn't take long for the legos, emissary, and D'Vinn to finish off what was left of my group and come after us.  We wisely decided to jump the moat and run around Trainer hill towards the Slaver house and exit that way, shouting HUGE TRAIN to zone all the way.  We make it the the cave entrance and lo and behold, guess who shows up.  luckily for us, not the poor brave souls who thought we were newbies running from cents.  One look at what we was chasing us and they ran for the zone, but not before we passed them, hence we made it to the zone, thanks to the people who tried to help us. And those of you who did help us, thanks you very much, or I surely would have lost my level. We made it safely with half a bubble left and no mana. Much to our chagrin, and that of the party running the other way, someone else was running from a train of cents and zoned just as we did, needless to say, some very shaken up newbies rezoned seconds later, to face the previous train that we and the rest of the zone crew was whacking on.  In the end, I was left with 17 hp and no mana, I medded up till I had enough to cast camo and then ran (walked more like it) to Kelethin to heal the rest of the way, thanking Tunare all the way.<br>
